ll see. Metro access within 300m. Buses and Trolleys run 50-100m from the house. There is a trolley that runs all night. Taxi is 35euros from the airport during the day. The center is roughly 20-25mins by train. I prefer to wait for you in the train station and walk you home so that you can have a first impression of the neighborhood and have your questions answered. ',23.7359,38.0222,'{Internet,\"Wireless Internet\",Breakfast,\"Elevator in Building\",Heating,\"Family/Kid Friendly\",\"Fire Extinguisher\",Essentials}',685975,1,'Private Room - Wi-Fi - Athens','Dim','https://a1.muscache.com/ac/users/685975/profile_pic/1403549768/original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&crop=w:w;*,*&crop=h:h;*,*&resize=225:*&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70','2011-06-10','Athens, Attica, Greece','I am 33, living in Athens, in a pretty central part that connects you by train to the centre (20 minutes). \n\nI have many interests and so little time. Currently, I study Spanish in the University and occasionally I work, sometimes from home.\n\nI like traveling and I am happy to explore new countries or cities every time. I prefer slow cities or small places rather than capitals and crowded tourist-oriented neighborhoods.\n\nI enjoy hosting people in Athens (we have Acropolis, yeahhh). I try to help my visitors by offering a map and advice on the city. I can also help you find some alternative places to visit, not only in Athens but all over the country.\n\nWhen you cannot travel yourself, hosting travelers is the next best thing :) \nI try to offer my guest some local food, sometimes homemade (like jam, pies, cookies). Depending on the time of the year I might have some Greek Feta cheese for you to taste, honey, virgin olive oil and olives, oranges.\n\nI like introducing people to Greek food, monuments, culture. If you like I will provide you with a map and give you some hints. \n\nWhen I have time and/or money, I travel but when I don\'t I prefer listening to music, watching movies from all countries and reading.\n\nI do not have a life motto :).......\n\n\n','within an hour',1.00,4,'Private room'),(7316501,'https://a1.muscache.com/ac/pictures/92903165/b31fc08c_original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&size=small&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70','https://a1.muscache.com/ac/pictures/92903165/b31fc08c_original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&size=medium&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70',38,'2',1,1,'Real Bed',0,-1,'Mnisikleous, Athina, 105 56, Greece','A cool apt on the most romantic Athenian road, underneath the Acropolis, 2\' walking distance from Monastiraki & 5\' from Syntagma station. Offers renovated,beautiful, bright rooms in any kind of flexible schedule; daily/weekly/bi-weekly on a vol disc. Really bright rooms on the most traditional Plaka pedestrian road. Walking distance to everywhere and the most well connected metro stations in Athens, Monastiraki (blue + green line) , Syntagma (where the airport bus starts from). all rooms, but the one I stay, if I am ta the house :) I will most likely be present at the listing during the guest\'s stay and happy to help in making an Athens sightseeing plan, if guests wish to have any city insights.  If you have any more questions about the apartment, please do not hesitate to contact me. I will be more than happy to help you! The safest and most quiet neighborhood in Athens. + the most traditional. You can see the Parthenon from different angles while walking around on the old Plaka roads',23.7282,37.9742,'{TV,Internet,\"Wireless Internet\",\"Air Conditioning\",Kitchen,Heating,Washer,Essentials,Shampoo}',866412,2,'Acropolis apt, 2\' from Monastiraki','Yiorgos','https://a1.muscache.com/ac/users/866412/profile_pic/1436787998/original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&crop=w:w;*,*&crop=h:h;*,*&resize=225:*&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70','2011-07-25','Athens, Attica, Greece','Love traveling, startups and particularly my startup :) and I love sharing experiences with people who come from different cultures & backgrounds.','within a few hours',1.00,1,'Private room'),(7353132,'https://a1.muscache.com/ac/pictures/93853415/e5a6e9d8_original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&size=small&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70','https://a1.muscache.com/ac/pictures/93853415/e5a6e9d8_original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&size=medium&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70',58,'4',2,2,'Real Bed',0,-1,'Athens, Attica 116 35, Greece','A fully furnished and totally renovated apartment in Pagrati, in the center of Athens.  Two bedrooms, two bathrooms, one big dinning room and a great kitchen!  You will enjoy its minimal decoration and its relaxing atmosphere for sure! The place!!',23.7467,37.9655,'{TV,Internet,\"Wireless Internet\",Kitchen,\"Pets Allowed\",Breakfast,\"Elevator in Building\",Heating,\"Family/Kid Friendly\",\"Suitable for Events\",Washer,\"First Aid Kit\",Essentials,Shampoo}',6566461,2,'Live your dream in Athens','Katerina','https://a2.muscache.com/ac/users/6566461/profile_pic/1369480073/original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&crop=w:w;*,*&crop=h:h;*,*&resize=225:*&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70','2013-05-25','Athens, Attica, Greece','I am Katerina, from Athens. I work and live in Cyprus. Working a lot with herbal teas, traditional products and mediterranean food. Love traveling to discuver new tastes...\nLoving photography and painting...Loving meeting new people and offer my hospitality!\nI will love to make new friends, so please feel free to ask me anything and visit my place!','within a day',1.00,1,'Entire home/apt'),(7376310,'https://a2.muscache.com/ac/pictures/93579720/ab179713_original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&size=small&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70','https://a2.muscache.com/ac/pictures/93579720/ab179713_original.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none&size=medium&output-format=jpg&output-quality=70',25,'2',1,1,'Real Bed',0,-1,'Ioustinianou, Athina, 114 73, Greece','Sunny flat in Exarheia, walkable to the center of the city, with a seperate bedroom. The 